# M6 countdown-fix — full pre-round 3-2-1-GO sequence visibility test.
#
# Uses the new `countdown_seconds 3` directive to extend countdown
# from the 1s shot-mode default to the interactive 3s. Captures the
# entire arc so the contact sheet shows:
#   * "3" through frames at t≈75-130 (after 1s lobby auto-start
#     fires at t=60 → COUNTDOWN starts ~t=70, "3" visible until ~t=130)
#   * "2" frames at t≈130-190
#   * "1" frames at t≈190-250
#   * "GO!" frames at t≈250-285 (~0.6s linger past phase flip)
# Numerals should be CRISP (UI_FONT_HUGE 192px atlas, was UI_FONT_DISPLAY
# 48px → blurry 5x upscale). GO! is gold-pulse, countdown is cream.
# Both backed by an 8-direction outline so they read on busy backdrops.

window 1280 720
seed 1 0
out build/shots/m6_countdown
network host 24700
name HostA
loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Sidearm" Light Standard
map slipstream
no_parallax
countdown_seconds 3

# Cover the full arc — auto_start_seconds defaults to 1s in shot mode
# so COUNTDOWN starts around t=60. With 3s countdown that runs to
# ~t=240; GO! lingers ~0.6s = 36 ticks past that.
burst t from 60 to 290 every 10

at 320 end

contact_sheet sheet cols 6 cell 320 180
